Welcome to another Forest Hex hacking adventure! Today&rsquo;s plan is to explore a retired CTF from http://hackthebox.eu named &ldquo;Beep&rdquo;. I chose this box because it&rsquo;s easy, it&rsquo;s linux, and it&rsquo;s rated very highly. All that put together should add up to some serious fun, so let&rsquo;s get started:
 Port Scan The first thing, as always, is a port scan:
#!/bin/bash ports=$(nmap -p- --min-rate=1000 -T4 $1 | grep ^[0-9] | cut -d '/' -f 1 | tr '\n' ',' | sed s/,$//) nmap -sC -sV -p$ports $1  Using my bash script we can ensure every port is checked, and that a deeper scan is only performed on open ports.
